OL,3,CRevealed: Stormont legal advice over
OL,4,C'controversial' Irish language signs
OL,6,FOn June 20th Mrs Kimmins replied
OL,7,Finsisting, again, that as
OL,8,FInfrastructure minister "any decision
OL,9,Fin relation to the provision of public
OL,10,Ftransport clearly falls within my
OL,11,Fremit."
OL,13,FIn reference to the legal action she
OL,14,Fwent on to say it would be "preferable
OL,15,Fif we discussed the matter to reach a
OL,16,Fbetter mutual understanding of our
OL,17,Fpositions before escalating this
OL,18,Fmatter unnecessarily".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
